#!/usr/local/bin/dyalogscript
⍝ Test suite for QR.Encode
⍝ Compares QR.Encode output against reference matrices generated by the
⍝ Python qrcode library. Uses manifest.json for test case definitions.
⍝
⍝ Usage:  dyalogscript test_qr.apls
⍝
⍝ Prerequisites:
⍝   python generate_test_references.py   ⍝ generates test_references/

⎕IO←0 ⋄ ⎕ML←1

⍝ ── Test harness ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
pass←0 ⋄ fail←0
check←{(name exp got)←⍵ ⋄ exp≡got:⊢(pass+←1)⊢⎕←'  ✓ ',name ⋄ ⊢(fail+←1)⊢⎕←'  ✗ ',name,' — expected ',(⍕exp),' got ',⍕got}
checkmat←{
    (name exp got)←⍵
    exp≡got:⊢(pass+←1)⊢⎕←'  ✓ ',name
    (⍴exp)≢⍴got:⊢(fail+←1)⊢⎕←'  ✗ ',name,' — shape: expected ',(⍕⍴exp),' got ',⍕⍴got
    diff←+/,exp≠got
    ⊢(fail+←1)⊢⎕←'  ✗ ',name,' — ',(⍕diff),' modules differ out of ',⍕×/⍴exp
}

⍝ ── Load QR namespace ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
⎕FIX 'file://QR/QR.apln'
:If 0=⎕NC'QR.Encode'
    ⎕←'FATAL: QR.Encode not found after Link.Import'
    ⎕OFF 1
:EndIf

⍝ ── Helpers ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
refdir←'test_references'

LoadRef←{
    ⍝ ⍵ = filename (relative to refdir)
    ⍝ Returns boolean matrix
    path←refdir,'/',⍵
    lines←⊃⎕NGET path 1
    lines←(0<≢¨lines)/lines
    '1'=↑lines
}

⍝ ── Load manifest ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
manifest←⎕JSON⊃⎕NGET(refdir,'/manifest.json')

⍝ ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
⎕←'=== QR.Encode Test Suite (',(⍕≢manifest),' test cases) ==='
⎕←''

:For tc :In manifest
    file←tc.file
    data←tc.data
    ec←tc.ec
    mask←tc.mask
    size←tc.size
    expShape←size size

    ⍝ Build left argument
    :If mask=¯1
        left←ec
    :Else
        left←ec mask
    :EndIf

    ⍝ Run encoder
    got←left QR.Encode data

    ⍝ Load reference
    ref←LoadRef file

    ⍝ Check shape and content
    _←check(file,' shape')(expShape)(⍴got)
    _←checkmat(file,' matrix')ref got
:EndFor

⍝ ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
⎕←''
⎕←'=== Results: ',(⍕pass),' passed, ',(⍕fail),' failed ==='
⎕OFF fail>0
